#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Kassapagottasutta "
msgstr "3. With Kassapagotta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn9.3:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā kassapagotto kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Kassapagotta was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/what-does-cheta-mean/3593
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.3:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā kassapagotto divāvihāragato aññataraṃ chetaṃ ovadati. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Kassapagotta, having withdrawn for his day’s meditation, tried to advise a tribal hunter. "

msgctxt "sn9.3:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā āyasmantaṃ kassapagottaṃ saṃvejetukāmā yenāyasmā kassapagotto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ kassapagottaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the deity haunting that forest approached Kassapagotta wanting to stir him up, and recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.428, sc2
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.1"
msgid "“Giriduggacaraṃ chetaṃ, "
msgstr "“A tribal hunter wandering the rugged hills "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.2"
msgid "appapaññaṃ acetasaṃ; "
msgstr "is unintelligent, unthinking. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.3"
msgid "Akāle ovadaṃ bhikkhu, "
msgstr "It’s a waste of time to advise him; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.4"
msgid "mandova paṭibhāti maṃ. "
msgstr "this mendicant seems to me like an idiot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.1"
msgid "Suṇāti na vijānāti, "
msgstr "The tribal hunter listens without understanding, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.2"
msgid "Āloketi na passati; "
msgstr "he looks without seeing. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.3"
msgid "Dhammasmiṃ bhaññamānasmiṃ, "
msgstr "Though the teaching is spoken, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.4"
msgid "Atthaṃ bālo na bujjhati. "
msgstr "the fool doesn’t get it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.199, sc4
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.1"
msgid "Sacepi dasa pajjote, "
msgstr "Even if you lit ten lamps "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.2"
msgid "dhārayissasi kassapa; "
msgstr "and brought them to him, Kassapa, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.3"
msgid "Neva dakkhati rūpāni, "
msgstr "he wouldn’t see anything, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.4"
msgid "cakkhu hissa na vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr "for he has no eyes to see.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn9.3:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā kassapagotto tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti. "
msgstr "Impelled by that deity, Venerable Kassapagotta was struck with a sense of urgency."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
